<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Since ZF's MVC approach builds up HTML with HTML code being generated from just about anywhere, I was wondering if it were possible to auto-execute a XHTML validation at the end of every page rendered during development, and then throw Exceptions when certain fragments are not valid for the defined DTD.</p>

<p>This could be a great help to keep pages valid when working with a lot of HTML-snippets etc...</p>

